atDhcpsn.name: atDhcpsn

revisions.description: MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.
This MIB file contains definitions of managed objects for DHCP Snooping in AlliedWare Plus.

atDhcpsn.description: Added two more violation types for DHCP Snooping.

atArpsecTrap.name: atArpsecTrap
atArpsecTrap.description: DHCP Snooping ARP Security violation trap.

atDhcpsnVariablesTable.name: atDhcpsnVariablesTable
atDhcpsnVariablesTable.description: This table contains rows of DHCP Snooping information.

atDhcpsnVariablesEntry.name: atDhcpsnVariablesEntry
atDhcpsnVariablesEntry.description: A set of parameters that describe the DHCP Snooping features.

atDhcpsnIfIndex.name: atDhcpsnIfIndex
atDhcpsnIfIndex.description: Ifindex of the port that the packet was received on.

atDhcpsnVid.name: atDhcpsnVid
atDhcpsnVid.description: VLAN ID of the port that the packet was received on.

atDhcpsnSmac.name: atDhcpsnSmac
atDhcpsnSmac.description: Source MAC address of the packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnOpcode.name: atDhcpsnOpcode
atDhcpsnOpcode.description: Opcode value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap. Only bootpRequest(1) or bootpReply(2) is valid.

atDhcpsnCiaddr.name: atDhcpsnCiaddr
atDhcpsnCiaddr.description: Ciaddr value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnYiaddr.name: atDhcpsnYiaddr
atDhcpsnYiaddr.description: Yiaddr value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnGiaddr.name: atDhcpsnGiaddr
atDhcpsnGiaddr.description: Giaddr value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnSiaddr.name: atDhcpsnSiaddr
atDhcpsnSiaddr.description: Siaddr value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnChaddr.name: atDhcpsnChaddr
atDhcpsnChaddr.description: Chaddr value of the BOOTP packet that caused the trap.

atDhcpsnVioType.name: atDhcpsnVioType
atDhcpsnVioType.description: The reason that the trap was generated. invalidBootp(1) indicates that the received BOOTP packet was invalid. For example, it is neither BootpRequest nor BootpReply. invalidDhcpAck(2) indicates that the received DHCP ACK was invalid. invalidDhcpRelDec(3) indicates the DHCP Release or Decline was invalid. invalidIp(4) indicates that the received IP packet was invalid. maxBindExceeded(5) indicates that if the entry was added, the maximum bindings configured for the port would be exceeded. opt82InsertErr(6) indicates that the insertion of Option 82 failed. opt82RxInvalid(7) indicates that the received Option 82 information was invalid. opt82RxUntrusted(8) indicates that Option 82 information was received on an untrusted port. opt82TxUntrusted(9) indicates that Option 82 would have been transmitted out an untrusted port. replyRxUntrusted(10) indicates that a BOOTP Reply was received on an untrusted port. srcMacChaddrMismatch(11) indicates that the source MAC address of the packet did not match the BOOTP CHADDR of the packet. staticEntryExisted(12) indicates that the static entry to be added already exists. dbAddErr(13) indicates that adding an entry to the database failed.

atArpsecVariablesTable.name: atArpsecVariablesTable
atArpsecVariablesTable.description: This table contains rows of DHCP Snooping ARP Security information.

atArpsecVariablesEntry.name: atArpsecVariablesEntry
atArpsecVariablesEntry.description: A set of parameters that describe the DHCP Snooping ARP Security features.

atArpsecIfIndex.name: atArpsecIfIndex
atArpsecIfIndex.description: Ifindex of the port that the ARP packet was received on.

atArpsecClientIP.name: atArpsecClientIP
atArpsecClientIP.description: Source IP address of the ARP packet.

atArpsecSrcMac.name: atArpsecSrcMac
atArpsecSrcMac.description: Source MAC address of the ARP packet.

atArpsecVid.name: atArpsecVid
atArpsecVid.description: VLAN ID of the port that the ARP packet was received on.

atArpsecVioType.name: atArpsecVioType
atArpsecVioType.description: The reason that the trap was generated. srcIpNotFound(1) indicates that the Sender IP address of the ARP packet was not found in the DHCP Snooping database. badVLAN(2) indicates that the VLAN of the DHCP Snooping binding entry associated with the Sender IP address of the ARP packet does not match the VLAN that the ARP packet was received on. badPort(3) indicates that the port of the DHCP Snooping binding entry associated with the Sender IP address of the ARP packet does not match the port that the ARP packet was received on. srcIpNotAllocated(4) indicates that the CHADDR of the DHCP Snooping binding entry associated with the Sender IP address of the ARP packet does not match the Source MAC and/or the ARP source MAC of the ARP packet.
